<task id="108" project="spaarke-multi-container-multi-index-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Code page: dropdown component (DV Web API) + side-pane redesign (replace 4 tabs; relocate Relevance Threshold + Search Mode; popup info icons)</title>
    <phase>G: Lookup-driven multi-index</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5-7</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>101</dependencies>
    <blocks>109</blocks>
    <tags>code-page, frontend, fluent-ui, react-18</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.tsx` files in side-pane + main App; introduces new service module + normalize utility; UX-visible changes. Code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Multiple files in same module — App.tsx, SearchPane, hooks all touch each other.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement the side-pane redesign from spec §6. (1) New `aiSearchIndexService.ts` — direct Dataverse Web API call for active `sprk_aisearchindex` rows (with `Prefer: odata.include-annotations` for the Choice FormattedValue). (2) New `targetEntityNormalize.ts` — `normalizeTargetEntityLabel` (lowercase + strip spaces) + `buildSearchRequestFragment` (Choice label → `{scope, entityType, searchIndexName}` fragment, with "All" → scope='all'). (3) Replace the 4 domain tabs (Documents/Matters/Projects/Invoices) at the top of the side pane with a single "Search Index" Dropdown sourced from the new service. (4) Move `Relevance Threshold` + `Search Mode` from the hidden top-right area INTO the side pane (below the existing filters, above Search button). (5) Convert any inline-help labels (`(i)` etc.) to Fluent UI v9 `Popover` triggered by `Info16Regular` icon. (6) Default selection precedence per spec §6: URL envelope → `sprk_isdefault=true` → first row alphabetically. (7) On-change triggers re-search with the new searchIndexName + entityType. (8) Wire request body to use `buildSearchRequestFragment` output.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Code-page (React 18 + Fluent UI v9) developer comfortable with `@spaarke/auth`, Dataverse Web API, and the existing `useSemanticSearch` / `useRecordSearch` hooks.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Code page side pane reflects spec §6 layout. Dropdown lists active `sprk_aisearchindex` rows by `sprk_displayname`. Selecting a row determines both `searchIndexName` AND entity filter (via `sprk_targetentitytype` Choice label normalize). `Relevance Threshold` + `Search Mode` are now in the side pane (discoverable). Popup `Info` icons replace inline-help labels.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/App.tsx</file>
