    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Dataverse Web API in code page" location="standard">
        `await fetch(${dataverseUrl}/api/data/v9.2/&lt;entityset&gt;?$select=...&amp;$filter=...&amp;$orderby=..., { headers: { Accept: 'application/json', 'OData-Version': '4.0', Prefer: 'odata.include-annotations="OData.Community.Display.V1.FormattedValue"' }, credentials: 'include' })`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Popover info icon" location="ADR-021">
        `&lt;Popover&gt;&lt;PopoverTrigger&gt;&lt;Button icon={&lt;Info16Regular /&gt;} appearance="transparent" /&gt;&lt;/PopoverTrigger&gt;&lt;PopoverSurface&gt;...&lt;/PopoverSurface&gt;&lt;/Popover&gt;`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/services/aiSearchIndexService.ts` per spec §6 with `AiSearchIndexRow` interface + `listActiveSearchIndexes()` function. Include the `Prefer: odata.include-annotations="OData.Community.Display.V1.FormattedValue"` header so FormattedValue comes through.</step>
    <step order="2">Create `src/client/code-pages/SemanticSearch/src/services/targetEntityNormalize.ts` per spec §6.5 with `normalizeTargetEntityLabel` + `buildSearchRequestFragment` + `ALL_SENTINEL` constant.</step>
    <step order="3">Add unit tests for `targetEntityNormalize.ts`: each known label → expected wire form ("Matter"→"matter", "Work Assignment"→"workassignment", "All"→null+scope='all', etc.). Boundary tests: empty label → null; whitespace-only → null.</step>
    <step order="4">Identify the current 4-domain-tab component in App.tsx (likely a `SearchDomain` enum + a TabList in the side pane). Replace with a Fluent v9 `Dropdown` populated by `listActiveSearchIndexes()`. The Dropdown calls `setActiveDomain` (or equivalent state) to a new shape: `{ searchIndexName, targetEntityType, displayName }`.</step>
    <step order="5">Default selection per spec §6: on mount, fetch active rows; pick the row matching URL envelope `searchIndexName` (if present); else the row with `sprk_isdefault=true`; else the first by `sprk_displayorder` then `sprk_displayname`. If empty list, show a "no indexes configured" disabled state (spec §6 Authorization).</step>
    <step order="6">Wire on-change: when user picks a different row, call existing `executeSearch` with the new fragment built from `buildSearchRequestFragment`. Cancel any in-flight search first.</step>
    <step order="7">Update the request-body construction in `useSemanticSearch.ts` + `useRecordSearch.ts` to use `buildSearchRequestFragment` output (scope, entityType, searchIndexName) instead of the prior hard-coded scope logic. Keep the existing flow (request body shape, fetch, response handling) unchanged otherwise.</step>
    <step order="8">Locate the current `Relevance Threshold` + `Search Mode` controls (likely in a Settings menu in the top-right). Move the controls into the side pane below the existing filters, above the Search button. Use the SAME control types (Slider for Threshold, Dropdown for Mode) — just relocated.</step>
    <step order="9">Convert any inline-help labels (e.g., text after a field name like "Filter to threshold (0.0-1.0)") to a Fluent v9 `Popover` triggered by an `Info16Regular` Button next to the label. Help text content moves into the PopoverSurface.</step>
    <step order="10">Add unit tests for `aiSearchIndexService.ts` (mock fetch; assert URL + headers; assert FormattedValue mapping into `sprk_targetentitytypeLabel`). Add component tests for the new Dropdown behavior (mount fetches; default selection precedence; on-change fires search).</step>
    <step order="11">Run `npm test` — all green. Run `npm run lint`.</step>
    <step order="12">Run code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5 (FULL rigor). Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 108 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

